# Hackathon 2026

## Overview

This project is a gatsby react app that generates a superhero character based on the user's answers to a set of quiz questions. The app uses a CSV file of all of the superhero characters and their stats, then applies a scoring algorithm in order to rank the users best matches. It is deployed on Netlify and can be accessed at https://serene-cheesecake-18f9f2.netlify.app/.

## Getting Started
Ensure that you have Node.js and npm installed on your machine. You can download them from [Node.js official website](https://nodejs.org/).

To get started, clone the repository and install the dependencies:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/HDDyer/Hackathon-2026
cd Hackathon-2026
npm install
```

Then, start the development server:

```bash
npm run develop
```

This will start the app at `http://localhost:8000`. You can then take the quiz and see your best superhero match!